The paper discusses the creation of an interactive game-player that continuously learns and improves, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The player's ability to interact with viewers and form opinions on popular game titles suggests a focus on game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The potential for live-streaming and accepting suggestions for strategies or games to play suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI).
